se.chalmers.ait.dat215.project
Class ShoppingCart

java.lang.Object
  se.chalmers.ait.dat215.project.ShoppingCart

public class ShoppingCart
extends java.lang.Object

The ShoppingCart holds ShoppingItems representing the products a customer has selected to buy. There is only one instance of this class in the system. It is possible to add and remove ShoppingItem and Product objects from the shoppingcart and also to get its current total cost.

addProduct

public void addProduct(Product p)
Add a Product to the ShoppingCart. Creates a ShoppingItem object where the amount of the product given as argument is 1.0 and adds this item to the cart. This method does not make any checks for if there are any shopping items containing the same product already in the shoppingcart.

See Also:
ShoppingItem

addProduct

public void addProduct(Product p,
                       double d)
Add a specific amount of a Product to the ShoppingCart. Creates a ShoppingItem object where the amount of the product given as argument is d and adds this item to the cart. This method does not make any checks for if there are any shopping items containing the same product already in the shoppingcart.

addShoppingCartListener

public void addShoppingCartListener(ShoppingCartListener scl)
Adds a listener for changes to the shopping cart. The listener gets notified whenever the shopping cart changes. This can be useful for instance for always keeping a visual presentation of the shopping cart up to date.
